1.title: Blink
1.plot: With the company mysteriously losing money left and right, the team gets excited when a high-profile client decides to give Find Love, NYC a try. However, crucial details are missed while they argue over the best path Mr. Harold Blink should take on his journey to love.

2.title: Belfast
2.plot: After the team's close call with Mr. Blink, Dr. Englebert's worldly experience is put under question when the team realizes that his gaydar is lacking or, more likely, missing all-together.

3.title: Sweaty Day
3.plot: What happens when the A/C at "Find Love, NYC" goes out, everyone is tired, hungry, hot, and grumpy, and an important lover of Samantha's shows up? Fun, love, and the uncovering of the money issue.

4.title: Free Love Day
4.plot: It's "Free Love Day" at Find Love, NYC and everybody's getting some. Will this plan save the company from going under? Will Samantha find love with Carter? Will Englebert do math?

5.title: Meet Street Is Coming
5.plot: Success (and love) is in the air for the Find Love, NYC crew. Clients and money are rolling in. Samantha is getting control of her pants. Englebert experiments again.

locations: Long Island City, New York, USA::(Entrepreneur Space)
imdb.plot outline: "I do four things every morning: Dance, find love, learn a new magic trick, and get out of bed... all in that order," writes Tristan Law, head consultant of Find Love, NYC, in his book: 'Tristan Law's Tristan's Law.' Tristan Law and a cast of wacky, oddball characters try to help singles find the perfect match, guide them through the dating process, and even help couples maintain their relationships in a city where love is almost as hard to find as a clean street corner. When money goes missing from the start up company, the overly positive Tristan Law tries to save it with no help from the one-track minded, sex obsessed owner, Samantha Medici. Complicating the matter is the rag-tag team of employees including Dr. Englebert, who may or may not even be a real doctor; Jolena, a consultant who lets her sordid New Jersey love life get in the way; Sebastian, the wry receptionist hopelessly in love with Tristan; Sophia, Jolena's best friend and Tristan's ex who doesn't even work there; and Chester, the janitor...who...well...Chester has problems. Can this group of misfits hold it together and save the company from financial ruin all while fulfilling their mission to help others find love and keep it?

'Love is in the air, just reach up and grab it!' says Tristan Law of the love consulting firm of _Find Love, NYC_ (qv). Tristan Law and a team of wacky, oddball characters try to help singles find the perfect match, guide them through the dating process, and even help couples maintain their relationships in a city where love is almost as hard to find as a clean street corner. When money goes missing from the love-based start-up company, it's up to the eccentric employees who are rarely on the same page, or even in the same book, to put aside their differences and come together to save _Find Love, NYC_ (qv) from almost certain financial ruin.::Sean Gallagher & Matthew Van Vorst
